cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about biomedical text mining using a pre-trained language model, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which could place it under cs.IR and cs.AI, respectively. Finally, the paper mentions the use of pre-training on large-scale biomedical corpora, which could also make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
